    "recap_headline": "Mississippi State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "STARKVILLE -\nSixth-ranked Mississippi State delivered another overpowering performance Tuesday, rolling past Jackson State 17-1 in seven innings at Dudy Noble Field as the 10-run rule brought an early end to the contest.\nThe Diamond Dawgs (17-4) combined explosive offense with dominant pitching, recording their third one-hitter of the season while piling up 12 hits and taking advantage of five Jackson State errors.\nMSU set the tone immediately in the first inning, loading the bases before\nNoah Sullivan\nand\nReed Stallman\neach lifted sacrifice flies to give the Bulldogs a 2-0 lead. The advantage quickly grew in the second, as State capitalized on defensive miscues and timely hitting to push across four runs, highlighted by Stallman's two-run single.\nThe Bulldogs never let up. In the third,\nJacob Parker\ndoubled and later scored, and the fourth inning turned into a decisive blow. The Diamond Dawgs erupted for five runs, with RBI contributions from\nGehrig Frei\nand Parker before\nBryce Chance\ncapped the inning with a two-run double to extend the lead to 12-0.\nOn the mound, Mississippi State was nearly flawless. Starter\nMaddox Miller\nallowed the lone hit over two scoreless innings while striking out three.\nParker Rhodes\n(1-0) followed with two perfect innings to earn the win. Jackson State's only run came in the fifth on a bases-loaded fielder's choice, but the Bulldogs' bullpen quickly shut the door, as\nTyler Pitzer\nand\nBrendan Sweeney\nfinished off two hitless frames.\nMSU answered in the bottom of the fifth with another five-run surge to put the game out of reach.\nDrew Wyers\ndelivered the biggest swing with a three-run double, while\nKevin Milewski\nand Frei added RBIs in the inning.\nParker led the Bulldogs at the plate, going 3-for-4 with three runs scored and an RBI. Frei added two hits and scored twice, while Wyers drove in three.\nAidan Teel\nreached base four times and crossed the plate three times as State showcased its depth throughout the lineup.\nThe Diamond Dawgs are set to host their first SEC series at home this weekend against Vanderbilt. The series begins on Friday at 7 p.m. on SEC Network.\nVisit\nwww.HailState.com\nfor the latest news and information on the baseball program. Fans can also follow the program on social media by searching 'HailStateBB' on\nX\n,\nFacebook\nand\nInstagram\n."
